Object.Field: LKM File to Sybase IQ (LOAD TABLE)

COMPONENT NAME: LKM File to Sybase IQ (LOAD TABLE)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Bulk Loads data from a flat file into Sybase AS IQ using the LOAD TABLE command. - This module sends a LOAD TABLE command to the Sybase IQ database so that the database will use the loading utility to load files.
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module assumes that the file being loaded is on the same box as the Sybase AS IQ server. - Date and Timestamp formats should be specified on source columns in the ODI COL_FORMAT field. - for date source column that have no col format, the KM will took the option: "DEFAULT_DATE_TIME_FORMAT"
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
The maximum amount of memory (in MB) that Sybase IQ will use to load the file.

This is the default format for date or time for source column when the column format is not set in the source datastore.
Sample DATE and DATETIME format options :
DATE ('MM/DD/YY') DATE ('YYYYMMDD')
DATETIME ('MMDDYYhhnnss') DATETIME ('hh:mm:ss MM-DD-YY') DATETIME ('hh:mm:ss') DATETIME ('MM/DD/YY hh:mm:ssaa')

create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] " + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL"), ",\n\t", "","")%> <% if (odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FORMAT]", "", "").equals("F")) {%>, SNP_PAD VARCHAR(100)<%}%> )

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<?
java.lang.String getDateFormat(java.lang.String pDataType, java.lang.String pcolFormat,java.lang.String pascii)
{

if (pDataType.equals("DATE")) 
		{
		if (pcolFormat.length()==0)
			return ("<%=odiRef.getOption( "DEFAULT_DATE_TIME_FORMAT" )%>");
		if ((pcolFormat.toUpperCase().indexOf("HH")>-1) ||(pcolFormat.toUpperCase().indexOf("NN")>-1) ||(pcolFormat.toUpperCase().indexOf("SS")>-1))
			return ("DATETIME('"+pcolFormat+"')");
		else
			return ("DATE('"+pcolFormat+"')");
		}
	else
	  return (pascii);
	}  
?>
<% if (odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FORMAT]", "", "").equals("D")) {%>
LOAD TABLE  <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%>     
(      
 <%=odiRef.getColList("\t", "[CX_COL_NAME]   <?= getDateFormat(\u0022[SOURCE_DT]\u0022,\u0022[COL_FORMAT]\u0022,\u0022\u0022) ?>", ",\n\t", "","")%>      
)  
FROM '<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[SCHEMA]/[RES_NAME]", "","")%>' 
QUOTES OFF    
ESCAPES OFF    
FORMAT ascii      
DELIMITED BY '\x<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_SEP_FIELD]", "", "")%>'
ROW DELIMITED BY '\x<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_SEP_ROW]", "", "")%>' 
SKIP <%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FIRST_ROW]", "", "")%> 
 
<%} else {%>
LOAD TABLE  <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "W")%>     
(  
 <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]   <?= getDateFormat(\u0022[SOURCE_DT]\u0022,\u0022[COL_FORMAT]\u0022,\u0022ASCII([BYTES])\u0022) ?>", ",\n\t", "","")%>
)  
FROM '<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[SCHEMA]/[RES_NAME]", "","")%>' 
QUOTES OFF    
ESCAPES OFF    
FORMAT ascii 
ROW DELIMITED BY '\x<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_SEP_ROW]", "", "")%>' 
SKIP <%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FIRST_ROW]", "", "")%> 
<% } %>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
